a.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/amitabh-bachchans-uyarntha-manithan-starts-from-march-20/articleshow/67737036.cms | access-date=April 2, 2019}}</ref>This film marks Bachchan's debut in Tamil cinema.\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Amitabh Bachchan]]\n*[[S. J. Surya]]\n*[[Ramya Krishnan]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Upcoming films]]\n[[Category:Indian multilingual films]]\n[[Category:Upcoming Tamil-language films]]\n\n\n{{Tamil-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{short description|Tamil-language film}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Uyarntha Manithan\n| director       = [[Tamilvannan]]\n| producer       = [[Bhushan Kumar]]<br>[[Krishan Kumar]]<br>[[Divya Khosla Kumar]]<br>[[Aanand L. Rai]]\n| writer         = Tamilvannan<br>[[Pon Parthiban]]\n| starring       = [[Amitabh Bachchan]]<br>[[S. J. Surya]]<br>[[Ramya Krishnan]]\n| editing        = [[Anthony (editor)|Anthony]]\n| music          = [[Ilaiyaraja]]\n| cinematography = [[Ravi Varman]]\n| studio         = [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n| distributor    = [[Colour Yellow Productions]]\n| released       = \n| runtime        = \n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n}}\n\n'''''Uyarntha Manithan''''' ({{translation|The noble man}}) is an upcoming Indian film directed by [[Tamilvannan]]. This film marks the reunion of Amitabh Bachchan and Ramya Krishnan after 21 years after their film ''[[Bade Miyan Chote Miyan]]'' that released in the year 1998 marking the last film of Ramya Krishnan in Bollywood.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/2019/apr/09/big-b-starrer-uyarndha-manithan--titled-tera-yaar-hoon-main--in-hindi-1961868.html|title=Amitabh Bachchan-starrer Uyarndha Manithan titled Tera Yaar Hoon Main in Hindi|website=The New Indian Express}}</ref> Principal filming started in March 2019.<ref name=\"Codingest 2019\">{{cite web | author=Codingest | title=Amitabh Bachchan starts sho